==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From French [[#French|grenade]], from Old French [[grenate]] in the phrase [[pome grenate]] ‘pomegranate’, ultimately from Latin [[pomum granatum]] ‘seeded fruit’.  The ''-d'' developed in French under influence of Spanish [[granada]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/grəˈneɪd/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪd|-eɪd]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# ''(obsolete)'' A [[pomegranate]].
# A small [[explosive]] [[device]], designed to be thrown by hand or launched from a grenade launcher.

